Here's the ViewModel using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (recommended approach — source generators handle all the boilerplate):

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isLoading;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        IsLoading = true;
        try
        {
            // Replace with your actual data service call
            var product = await FetchProductAsync();
            Name = product.Name;
            Price = product.Price;
            IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
        }
        finally
        {
            IsLoading = false;
        }
    }

    private async Task<(string Name, decimal Price, bool IsAvailable)> FetchProductAsync()
    {
        await Task.Delay(500); // simulate network
        return ("Widget", 29.99m, true);
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public properties (`Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable`, `IsLoading`) with `PropertyChanged` notifications, plus a `LoadCommand` of type `IAsyncRelayCommand`.

**XAML usage** — note `x:DataType` at the root for compiled bindings:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16" Spacing="12">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='Available: {0}'}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding IsLoading}" />
        <Button Text="Load Product" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**
- `[ObservableProperty]` generates the public property + `PropertyChanged` raise
- `[RelayCommand]` generates `LoadCommand` (disables the button automatically while running)
- `x:DataType` enables compiled bindings (8–20× faster, AOT-safe)
- Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to catch binding errors at build time

**NuGet:** `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (≥ 8.0)
